            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "There's a known circular reference in the Limited API Cyfunction implementation.\n\nLooking at it again, I think we can eliminate it, and it may well be worthwhile from a speed point of view anyway (it'll remove a layer of indirection in most cyfunc calls). I'll give that ago.\n\nI'd be generally a bit careful about relying too much on the order of destruction from Python refcounting - it obviously isn't robust in alternative implementations, and I know destruction does sometimes get deferred in the freethreading where objects have been accessed from multiple threads.",
